sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Ingress as KServe Ingress<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant Istio as Istio Sidecar<br/>mTLS STRICT
    participant Orchestrator as FMS Guardrails<br/>Orchestrator

    Note over Client,Orchestrator: Flow 1: Built-in Content Detection

    participant BuiltIn as Built-in Detector<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    Client->>Ingress: POST /api/v1/text/contents<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+
    Ingress->>Istio: Forward request<br/>mTLS
    Istio->>Orchestrator: Route to orchestrator
    Orchestrator->>BuiltIn: POST /api/v1/text/contents<br/>HTTP/8080 mTLS (Istio)<br/>Bearer Token (KServe auth)
    Note right of BuiltIn: Local evaluation:<br/>regex PII, file-type,<br/>custom detectors
    BuiltIn-->>Orchestrator: Detection results<br/>HTTP/mTLS
    Orchestrator-->>Client: Aggregated response

    Note over Client,Orchestrator: Flow 2: HuggingFace Model Inference

    participant S3 as S3 Storage (MinIO)<br/>9000/TCP HTTP
    participant HF as HuggingFace Detector<br/>8000/TCP HTTP

    Note right of S3: Init: KServe storage initializer<br/>downloads model weights
    S3-->>HF: Model artifacts<br/>HTTP/9000 AWS credentials

    Orchestrator->>HF: POST /api/v1/text/contents<br/>HTTP/8000 mTLS (Istio)<br/>Bearer Token (KServe auth)
    Note right of HF: Local inference:<br/>PyTorch model<br/>(SeqClass/TokClass/CausalLM)
    HF-->>Orchestrator: Classification results<br/>HTTP/mTLS

    Note over Client,Orchestrator: Flow 3: LLM Judge Evaluation

    participant Judge as LLM Judge Detector<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant vLLM as vLLM Server<br/>8080/TCP HTTP

    Orchestrator->>Judge: POST /api/v1/text/contents<br/>HTTP/8000 mTLS (Istio)<br/>Bearer Token (KServe auth)
    Judge->>vLLM: OpenAI-compatible request<br/>HTTP/8080 No encryption<br/>No auth (cluster-internal)
    vLLM-->>Judge: LLM evaluation response
    Judge-->>Orchestrator: Judge verdict<br/>HTTP/mTLS

    Note over Client,Orchestrator: Monitoring

    participant Prom as Prometheus

    Prom->>BuiltIn: GET /metrics (8080/TCP)
    BuiltIn-->>Prom: trustyai_guardrails_* counters
    Prom->>HF: GET /metrics (8000/TCP)
    HF-->>Prom: trustyai_guardrails_* counters
    Prom->>Judge: GET /metrics (8000/TCP)
    Judge-->>Prom: trustyai_guardrails_* counters
